title: Print, "Gouvernement General de Bretagne", 1751
creditline: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
description: Escutcheon with the title of the map of Brittany in "Atlas Universel" by Robert de Vaugondy, Paris, 1757.  the left bottom corner of the map.  The escutcheon is decorated with, and surrounded by, emblems of sea and commerce.

tombstone.epitaph:
Print, "Gouvernement General de Bretagne", 1751.
1751. Etching. Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt. 1925-2-564.
